The paper discusses the use of a queuing model to simulate airport departure processes and optimize gate assignments to reduce gate conflicts. This involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of robust gate assignment, which involves maximizing the time gap between two consecutive flights at the same gate, which can be seen as a control engineering problem (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data analysis and modeling techniques, which are commonly associated with computer engineering (cs.CE) and information theory (cs.IT).
